REASONING: MaxiCash is a pawnbroking service in Singapore that accepts jewellery, designer bags, and luxury watches for cash, as confirmed on their official website
The MaxiCash website specifically lists only three categories of items they buy: Jewellery, Designer Bags, and Luxury Watches
There is no mention of COE (Certificate of Entitlement) or vehicles being accepted at MaxiCash on their official website
COE is a certificate that gives the right to own and use a vehicle in Singapore for 10 years, as explained by the LTA website
While COEs can be transferred in certain categories (Categories C and E), this is done through official LTA channels, not through pawnshops
Search results about selling cars with COE refer to selling the entire vehicle through car dealerships or private sales, not selling the COE certificate itself at pawnshops
